M||tx|---
M|Hois|tx|Extract static JSX outside cp to avoid re-creation.
M|Hois|**In|**
M|Hois|tx|```tsx
M|Hois|tx|fn LoadingSkeleton() {
M|Hois|tx|return <div className="animate-pulse h-20 bg-gray-200" />
M|Hois|tx|}
M|Hois|tx|fn Container() {
M|Hois|tx|return (
M|Hois|tx|<div>
M|Hois|tx|{loading && <LoadingSkeleton />}
M|Hois|tx|</div>
M|Hois|tx|)
M|Hois|tx|}
M|Hois|tx|```
M|Hois|**Co|**
M|Hois|tx|```tsx
M|Hois|tx|const loadingSkeleton = (
M|Hois|tx|<div className="animate-pulse h-20 bg-gray-200" />
M|Hois|tx|)
M|Hois|tx|fn Container() {
M|Hois|tx|return (
M|Hois|tx|<div>
M|Hois|tx|{loading && loadingSkeleton}
M|Hois|tx|</div>
M|Hois|tx|)
M|Hois|tx|}
M|Hois|tx|```
M|Hois|tx|This is esp helpful for large and static SVG nodes, which can be expensive to recreate on every render.
M|Hois|**No|** If your project has [rc Compiler](https://rc.dv/learn/rc-compiler) enabled, the compiler automatically hoists static JSX elements and optimizes cp re-renders, making manual hoisting unnecessary.